================================================================================
ATTRIBUTION NOTICE
================================================================================

This repository is derived from and builds upon the following open-source
projects. Original copyright and rights belong to their respective authors.
The MIT License above applies ONLY to the modifications and additions made
in this repository (specifically, the Scope Reconstruction and Map Correction
integration code, configuration files, documentation, and benchmark scripts
created by the copyright holder above).

1. NACLIP (Neighbour-Aware CLIP)
   - Author: Sina Hajimiri, Ismail Ben Ayed, Jose Dolz
   - Repository: https://github.com/sinahmr/NACLIP
   - Paper: "Pay Attention to Your Neighbours: Training-Free Open-Vocabulary
     Semantic Segmentation," WACV 2025 (arXiv:2404.08181)
   - License at the time of use: not explicitly specified in the upstream
     repository. This project uses the code under fair academic-use
     conventions, with this attribution notice serving as acknowledgment.

2. CorrCLIP (the source of the Scope Reconstruction and Map Correction
   modules that are re-implemented and ported into NACLIP in this repo)
   - Authors: Dengke Zhang, Fagui Liu, Quan Tang
   - Repository: https://github.com/zdk258/CorrCLIP
   - Paper: "CorrCLIP: Reconstructing Patch Correlations in CLIP for
     Open-Vocabulary Semantic Segmentation," ICCV 2025 (Oral)
     (arXiv:2411.10086)

3. SCLIP (transitive dependency, NACLIP is based on SCLIP)
   - Paper: "SCLIP: Rethinking Self-Attention for Dense Vision-Language
     Inference," ECCV 2024

4. CLIP (OpenAI), MMSegmentation (OpenMMLab), DINO, SAM2 (Meta AI) — used
   as building blocks; please refer to their original licenses.

If you use this repository, please cite the original NACLIP and CorrCLIP
papers in addition to acknowledging this work.
